  "name": "savesuspend-resume",
  "description": "Deep write->reload proof for issue #2's final slice: from the existing debugtools-hub-modern-debug Chapter 2 launcher route (frames 0..14766 replayed identically), exhausts the scripted post-launch rescue-unit dialogue (25 spaced A taps, frames 15100..16986), moves the cursor one tile right onto an empty 'Peak' tile, opens the ordinary in-game Map Menu (A), navigates to 'Suspend' (4x DOWN) and confirms it (A -> 'Do you want to quit?' -> Yes -> A), which runs the real PlayerPhase_Suspend / MapMenu Suspend command's WriteSuspendSave() -- not a test hook. A Player-Phase-start automatic auto-suspend has already written one SaveBlockInfo/SuspendSaveBlock slot earlier in the run (vanilla FE7/FE8 behavior); this manual Suspend is proven distinct because it lands in the *other* alternating slot with a different checksum and a cursor position (xCursor=9,yCursor=4) matching the live cursor at the moment of the manual command, not the auto-save's earlier cursor position. The scenario then triggers the ordinary soft-reset key combo (A+B+SELECT+START), confirms genuine reboot (Nintendo logo), and replays the same cold-boot A/START tap cadence used by savecompat-current.json to reach the save menu, where a valid Suspend save makes 'Resume Chapter' the reachable path -- loading through the ordinary ReadSuspendSave(), never a direct C test hook. The final checkpoint proves gPlaySt.chapterIndex/faction/xCursor/yCursor and a unit item probe were all restored to exactly the manually-saved values, not the stale auto-save's.",
